        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add defensive check for channel runtime initialization #87646",
        "body": "## What\n\nFixes #87646. Ensures missing `core.channel.inbound.run` during Feishu cold starts produces a retryable non-2xx response instead of silently dropping messages.\n\n## How — Error Propagation Chain\n\nThe fix ensures runtime-not-ready errors propagate through **all 4 handler layers** to the webhook HTTP response:\n\n1. **`getChannelInboundRun()`** (bot.ts) — throws when `core.channel.inbound.run` is missing\n2. **`handleFeishuMessage()`** catch (bot.ts) — selectively rethrows `channel runtime not ready`\n3. **`processMessage()`** catch (monitor.message-handler.ts) — selectively rethrows so the webhook handler gets the error\n4. **Broadcast paths** (bot.ts) — sequential: rethrows per-agent; parallel: propagates if ALL agents fail\n\nAll 3 dispatch paths (DM, broadcast-active, broadcast-observer) are covered.\n\n## Test\n\nUpdated regression test expects `rejects.toThrow(/channel runtime not ready/)`.\n\n## Behavioral Proof\n\nWhen `core.channel.inbound.run` is undefined:\n- Guard throws with diagnostic log (channel/inbound key state)\n- Error propagates through all handler layers (4 selective rethrows)\n- Webhook handler returns non-2xx → Feishu retries the message\n- Dedupe claim is released before rethrow (no stale locks)\n- Messages are NOT dropped or marked as processed\n\n> **Note:** Live Feishu gateway proof is not available in this contributor's environment (WeChat/Telegram only). The fix is validated through source analysis, handler chain tracing, and mocked tests. A maintainer with a Feishu gateway can verify by checking that cold-start messages produce retryable 5xx responses.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Lines | Description |\n|------|-------|-------------|\n| `bot.ts` | +34/-5 | `getChannelInboundRun` throws + 3 guard call sites + outer catch rethrow + broadcast rethrow |\n| `bot.test.ts` | +37/-1 | Updated regression test |\n| `monitor.message-handler.ts` | +5/-1 | `processMessage()` catch rethrow |\n",
